text: I love how the title seems to already make Maleficent a villain but I've never seen her that way, and I don't think the movie will make her seem evil either. Sure she overreacts, but she's seen firsthand what mankind can do when it comes to manipulation and love. So when her real love, Aurora, is seen to find love with the same kind of royalty who hurt her, of course she'll be suspicious. Especially since the Queen seems to harbor extreme hatred for Maleficent and non-humans, and isn't willing to set that aside for the sake of her son. I think at the end of the day, Maleficent believes that her method of lashing out wasn't just to defend the possible threat on her daughter, but the threat on non-human kind.   With Maleficent meeting her kind though, I think they're going to try to prevent her from interacting with humans or her home again. And in return, she'll either lash out and hurt them or make some kind of deal. But I bet she'll be some kind of special version of her kind, so they may regard her as a version of royalty.

text: "DON'T ruin my morning." Oooooh, man. It's not often I look forward to movies like this, but honestly? I'm really looking forward to it. I like the whole "redemption" schtick that kind of went down in the first Maleficent, but NOTHING is more satisfying than a follow up to a redemption story. Because, no one changes on a dime. Or even after a few years. Old habits are so, so very easy to fall back on. And Maleficent is very much that sort of character who thrives while she's toeing the line between unforgivable and not. She's not a good person, but you can't say she's pure, irredeemably evil, either. And I really hope this movie can explore that depth in character growth.    Also?? I just like these kinds of characters. Characters like Orochimaru, from Naruto (yes NARUTO), that are ambiguously evil and yet show startling growth. EVERYONE changes eventually. Even people like them. Loki, Draco Malfoy (even if his character imho was sort of underdeveloped and underused for the position he could have taken as a gray character), etc etc.    (also if anyone has any other characters like these ones i'm curious to see them because I'm  always looking for new fandoms)

text: I have a theory that the Queen is the true "Mistress of Evil". In the first movie, Maleficent became so much more relatable and wasn't this heartless, evil fairy-witch for no reason like the original version. I don't think they'd backtrack on that level of character development now. While yes, it is FUCKING AMAZING to see Maleficent be a total badass and I fucking love it, I don't think she's truly evil here; I think that with her backstory and with the events of this new film that she will be a relatable villain, like the kind where you don't know if you should or shouldn't root for. But the Queen... she's obviously a bag of hate, prove me wrong. I don't like her one single bit, I'm kinda really rooting for Maleficent in this one (again)!
